description: Number of primitive (period n) periodic palindromic structures using exactly four different symbols.
references: M. R. Nester (1999). Mathematical investigations of some plant interaction designs. PhD Thesis. University of Queensland, Brisbane, Australia.
formula: A056515(n)-A056514(n).This is the Moebius transform of A056510. - _T. D. Noe_, Oct 25 2006
example: For example, aaabbb is not a (finite) palindrome but it is a periodic palindrome. Permuting the symbols will not change the structure.
author: Marks R. Nester (nesterm(AT)dpi.qld.gov.au)
